<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>bench warmer • chair warmer</xh5><p> <i>bench warmer</i>—(coll.) a substitute in a sports team who seldom plays: He thought about leaving after the 1994 season, his third straight year as a <u>bench-warmer</u>.</p><p><i>chair warmer</i>—(coll.) 1. <i>(derog.)</i> an ineffective office holder or employee: The judge frowned at me. The courtroom <u>chair warmers</u> craned necks in my direction. 2. <i>(pejor.)</i> a person who lounges for long periods sitting in a chair: He never takes me out anywhere. He’s a <u>chair-warmer</u> at home for fair.</p><p> <i>See also: keep the seat warm / warm the bench.</i></p> </entry>
